An interesting test would be to get a level 60 rogue with decent gear and test our mitigation against them on the same mobs. That would give us an idea of whether our mitigation is &quot;chain class&quot;, higher or lower. Perhaps the rogues have even done these parses themselves?<br>
<br>
This is not quite the same as soloability. Monks can self buff their haste whereas rogues can't (and the T-staff proc helps). But if rogue tanking is about the same as ours, and chaotic stab is about equal to flying kick, then the distance between them in soloability has really shrunk.<br>
